<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="1709" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1709">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 834.00/132.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-02">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 2, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Diplomatic Corps recognize new provisional Government, except Brazilian
                            Minister, awaiting instructions. I believe our Government should
                            recognize the new Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grevstad.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>